1 2. An individual may not participate directly or indirectly in the nomination for more than
2 one individual for each office to be filled. The final filing date for nominating petitions is
3 no later than four p.m. sixty-four days before the day of the election.
4 3. Upon receipt of the petition or the certification as provided in this section, the county
5 auditor shall place, without fee, the name of the candidate so nominated on the
6 no-party ballot at the ensuing general election.
7 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Subsection 1 of section 4.1-20-18 of the North Dakota Century
8 Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
9 1. At each general election, one district supervisor must be elected for a term of six
10 years, or until the successor is duly elected and qualified, to each expiring or vacant
11 term. The county auditor of the county or counties in which the district lies shall return
12 to the secretary of state before four p.m. on the tenth day following any general
13 election a certified abstract of the votes cast in the county at the election for each
14 candidate for district supervisor. The secretary of state shall canvass the returns and
15 issue certificates of election under chapter 16.1-15canvass the returns and issue
16 certificates of election under chapter 16.1 - 15. When a district lies in more than one
17 county, the county auditor of the county in which the candidate resides shall issue the
18 certificate of election.
